# MeDoc — Operating context for this work session

## Project
MeDoc is a Tauri 2 + React 19 + TS desktop app for German dental
practices (Bachelorarbeit prototype, regulatory-aligned). Backend
in app/src-tauri (Rust, sqlx + SQLite/SQLCipher, audit-chained).
Frontend in app/src.

## Roles in this system (do not invent new ones)
- ARZT: full clinical + admin access. Source of medical truth.
- REZEPTION: operational front desk. NO medical content access.
  Owns patient master data, appointments, payments, intake.
- STEUERBERATER and PHARMABERATER: EXTERNAL roles. For this work,
  these roles must be visible in role lists only as "deaktiviert /
  externer Kontakt — Kommunikation per Beleg/PDF". Do not build
  in-app interactions for them. Do not delete the Rust RBAC entries
  — gate at the FE login + sidebar level only. The audit/RBAC
  matrix in app/src-tauri stays intact.

## Hard rules — never violate
1. Backend Rust is the source of truth for DTOs, RBAC, validation,
   audit. When in doubt, change FE to match BE. Never weaken BE
   checks.
2. No patient-identifying data in localStorage. Use SQLite via
   app_kv (whitelisted keys) or proper tables. Audit-relevant
   writes must produce audit entries.
3. No silent error swallowing. Every catch toasts, logs via
   logging.controller, or has an explicit /* ignore: <reason> */.
4. RBAC: for any FE gating change, mirror in
   app/src-tauri/src/application/rbac.rs allowed() AND in
   src/lib/rbac.ts ROUTE_VISIBILITY + NAV_ITEM_DEFINITIONS.
   Otherwise it's a regression.
5. No raw printing of HTML to a popup window for medical/financial
   documents. Use the existing render_invoice_pdf pipeline
   (FA-FIN-INVOICE) or extend it. Anything user-printable goes
   through PDF, never window.print() of unescaped HTML.
6. Use design-system primitives in views/components/ui/* for
   buttons, inputs, dialogs, cards, toasts, badges, empty states.
   No raw <button>/<input>/<div role=dialog>.
7. Inline style only for one-off layout numbers. Never for color,
   spacing tokens, fonts, radii — those come from CSS variables in
   index.css (--fg, --fg-2, --fg-3, --line, --accent, --red,
   --orange, --blue, --green, --surface-1, --surface-2,
   --shadow-lg, --radius-ctl, etc).
8. UI text in German (Sie-Form). Code, comments, commit messages,
   identifiers in English.
9. Currency formatCurrency() and dates formatDate/formatDateTime
   from lib/utils.ts. No hand-rolled de-DE.
10. No new dependencies without justifying why existing ones
    (zod, zustand, react-router-dom, date-fns, clsx, tailwind-merge,
    local lib/icons.tsx) cannot do the job.

## Working method
- Read relevant files BEFORE writing. Reference docs in
  /docs (rbac-matrix.md, benutzerhandbuch.md, architecture-design.md,
  07-iso-22600-dsgvo.md, 02-use-case-diagram.md).
- For each task, list files you will touch first, then execute.
  Do not edit files outside the announced list without asking.
- After each phase: run `npm run typecheck`, `npm test`,
  `cargo check --manifest-path app/src-tauri/Cargo.toml`. All
  three must pass before declaring the phase done.

## Definition of done (every change)
[ ] typecheck clean, tests green, cargo check clean
[ ] No new console.error/warn in normal flows
[ ] Keyboard navigable, focus visible, aria-label on icon-only
    controls, role on dialogs/menus, <label htmlFor> on inputs
[ ] No new inline color/spacing literals — uses CSS variables
[ ] Supports data-density="compact|cozy|spacious" and dark
    sidebar tone
[ ] If RBAC-relevant, mirrored FE + BE
[ ] If app_kv keys added, whitelisted in permission_for()
[ ] If a workflow change, the use case in 02-use-case-diagram.md
    is updated

## When uncertain
Stop and ask. Do not invent backend commands, DTO fields, RBAC
keys, i18n keys, or rules. Do not "improve" semantics by guessing.